Neema Hospital in Kitui town has scooped the top award as a Tunza centre of excellence, surpassing 30 health facilities that are members of the Tunza Family Healthcare Network in lower Eastern. The private facility got the top honours for providing quality healthcare. It had been nominated by heath NGO PS Kenya that operates under the Health ministry to improve services. On Friday, Neema director Kinako Musembi received the award from PS Kenya manager Diana Mwiti — in charge of quality assurance. The ceremony was held at Talents Hotel, Kitui town. Mwiti represented PS Kenya CEO Joyce Wanderi. She praised the hospital for its efforts to improve care. “Your hard work has paid off and your accomplishments speak for themselves. Congratulations,” Mwiti said.